2026-04-21 01:35:31 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['load_module_internal_wiring'] hypothesis_explanation='Inspection of the load module shows that although the positive input rail from Control Module 8 reaches the anode of the series diode, the diode cathode is not connected anywhere, and both the main lamp and the internal indicator lamp have only their negative terminals connected. In other words, the positive side of both lamps is left floating and the diode output is open-circuit. This miswiring makes it impossible for current to flow through either lamp regardless of upstream module status, while leaving all other module indications unaffected. Correct wiring should connect the diode cathode to the positive terminals of both lamps (with the lamp negatives on the negative rail). Repairing this internal wiring fault in the load module should restore lamp operation when 12 V is present and the control switches are on.'
