Instruction: Electrically test the continuity of the two series rails between Control Module 8 and the Load Module by temporarily bypassing the load circuitry. Disconnect the two input cables from the Load Module and directly connect them together (positive to positive rail, negative to negative rail) using a jumper or temporary connector, effectively extending the series chain past module 8 with no load. Then, with the battery inserted and all switches ON, check whether any of the control-module indicator LEDs (especially module 8’s) change behavior or turn on, and note if any module or cable shows signs of heating or intermittent connection.
