2026-04-21 01:35:52 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control_module_6_switch_input_connection'] hypothesis_explanation="Inspection of control modules 2–8 showed that all positive and negative rails are continuous and with correct polarity, except at Control Module 6. There, Control Input Cable (+) 6 is left floating at port 'n' and is not connected to the internal switch/indicator circuit. This produces an open circuit in the +12 V rail at module 6. As a result, no downstream control-module indicators receive supply and the load module never sees voltage, even though the PSU LED is on and all switches are set to ON. Restoring the connection from Control Input Cable (+) 6 to the Control Module 6 switch/indicator 12 V line should re-establish continuity and allow the lamp and downstream indicators to operate."
